Agnes Vernon https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agnes_Vernon 0 Agnes 'Brownie' Vernon (December 27, 1895 – February 21, 1948) was an American actress of the silent era. She appeared in 90 films between 1914 and 1921. She made a number of films in Australia, having been brought out there by Snowy Baker and E.J. Carroll. She was born in La Grande, Oregon and died in San Diego, California. Agnes_'_Brownie_'_Vernon ( December_27_,_1895 – February_21_,_1948 ) was an_American_actress of the_silent_era .
